research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0068.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` did not fail on quality grounds; it failed because the execution layer still rejects the architecture name before training starts. The smallest informative move is a narrow code-fix round inside `sparsify/` that registers and wires `lowrank_residual` into config validation and SAE class dispatch so the intended K=128 proxy prototype can finally produce a real signal.","summary":"Register and implement the `lowrank_residual` architecture in `sparsify/`, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the blocker-first guidance by fixing the concrete architecture-selection failure instead of drawing conclusions from a non-run. The main risk is that additional compatibility issues appear after registration, but clearing the explicit selection gate is still the correct next step and keeps the architecture hypothesis intact.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 67 produced a concrete architecture-registration blocker for `lowrank_residual`: the runtime still rejects the architecture name in config validation before training begins.","This is stronger evidence of incomplete code integration than of a bad architecture, so `lowrank_residual` still has no usable quality signal.","The next round should keep the original `lowrank_residual` K=128 proxy target fixed and change only the code needed to make the family selectable and runnable by the existing launcher."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` runs and shows competitive proxy FVU, keep the family alive and stabilize its trunk width next.","If it runs cleanly but is clearly worse than gated and not better than prior archived families, archive it quickly and move to another genuinely new family.","If it still fails after registration and dispatch are fixed, treat the remaining issue as a deeper implementation incompatibility and shift effort elsewhere."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
