research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The obvious gated one-parameter sweep is now exhausted after clean regressions on both lower LR and lower expansion, so the next least-bad informative move is to unblock the incubating `factorized_topk` family rather than introduce another fresh direction. Its only evidence so far is a `sanity_failed` prototype, which should be treated as an architecture-compatibility issue, not a quality result. A narrow code fix inside `sparsify/` to make `factorized_topk` forward/backward compatible with the runtime should recover one valid proxy measurement at K=128 under the existing strongest regime.","summary":"Fix the `factorized_topk` implementation in `sparsify/` so it passes sanity, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the current priority order: resolve the blocked sanity failure on an already-incubating family before expanding the search space again. The main risk is spending a round on implementation recovery for a family that still underperforms, but one clean run is necessary before making any architecture judgment.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The gated exploitation sweep has now tested the remaining obvious one-parameter moves at K=128 and both lower LR and lower expansion regressed cleanly.","`factorized_topk` still has no usable quality signal because its first prototype failed at sanity, so it should not be treated as an architecture-quality miss yet.","This round keeps the original `factorized_topk` proxy target and changes only the architecture code needed for forward/backward compatibility under the fixed runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `factorized_topk` run completes and beats plain `topk`, keep the family alive and stabilize its internal factorization width or activation design next.","If the repaired run completes normally but remains far behind gated, retire shallow factorization and move to a different encoder-expressivity direction such as low-rank-plus-residual or routed multi-branch designs.","If `factorized_topk` still fails sanity after the focused fix, conclude that this prototype path is currently not viable in the stack and shift effort to another architecture family with a cleaner integration path."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0049.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`factorized_topk` has now failed for a concrete architecture-registration reason rather than an ambiguous quality or runtime signal: the execution layer rejects the architecture name in `SparseCoderConfig` before training begins. The next coherent move is a narrow code-fix round that wires `factorized_topk` into the existing config/class registry and forward path so the prototype can finally receive one real K=128 proxy measurement under the strongest current regime.","summary":"Register and enable the `factorized_topk` architecture in `sparsify/`, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the smallest defensible next step because the latest failure is an explicit compatibility bug, not a quality result, and continuing to retry without fixing registration would waste rounds. The main risk is that the family still underperforms once it runs, but one valid proxy result is required before deciding whether to stabilize or retire it.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 48 produced a concrete execution-layer error for `factorized_topk`: the architecture name is not registered in `SparseCoderConfig`, so the family still has no usable quality signal.","This is stronger evidence of a missing code integration step than of a bad architecture, so the family should not be retired on quality grounds yet.","This round keeps the original `factorized_topk` K=128 proxy target fixed and changes only the code needed to make the architecture selectable and runnable by the existing launcher."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registered `factorized_topk` run completes and beats plain `topk`, keep the family alive and begin stabilizing its internal factorization design.","If the run completes normally but remains far behind gated, retire shallow factorization and move to a different encoder-expressivity direction.","If `factorized_topk` still fails after registration is fixed, treat the remaining issue as a deeper implementation incompatibility and shift effort elsewhere."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
