se 'cpu'; try:\n    import torch_npu; device = 'npu' if torch.npu.is_available() else device\nexcept ImportError: pass; cfg = SparseCoderConfig(architecture='factorized_topk', k=128, expansion_factor=16); sae = SparseCoder(1024, cfg, device=device, dtype=torch.float32); x = torch.randn(4, 1024, device=device); out = sae(x); out.fvu.backward(); print('sanity: OK')"], "stdout_excerpt": "", "stderr_excerpt": "  File \"<string>\", line 1\n    import sys; sys.path.insert(0, '.'); from sparsify import SparseCoder; from sparsify.config import SparseCoderConfig; import torch; device = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'; try:\n                                                                                                                                                                                                 ^^^\nSyntaxError: invalid syntax", "traceback_excerpt": "  File \"<string>\", line 1"}}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:666:{"event_id": "evt_1774098736511829510", "ts": 1774098736, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 47, "session_id": "019d1063-2295-7e80-8596-03d10ee10dc8", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "factorized_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d1063-2295-7e80-8596-03d10ee10dc8", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "factorized_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_perf_code", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "The straightforward gated hyperparameter sweep has now produced only clean regressions, so the next informative move is to recover the blocked incubating family rather than spend another round on weak local tuning. `factorized_topk` still has no usable quality signal because its only attempt failed at sanity. A narrow architecture-compatibility fix inside `sparsify/` should let the same K=128 proxy prototype run and finally reveal whether extra encoder mixing can improve over plain top-k."}}
