research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five rounds of gated-local tuning have failed to move the frontier, so the current search direction is likely locally exhausted. The least-disruptive fundamentally different probe is to switch the single primary variable back to architecture and run `jumprelu` at K=128 under the strongest shared signum recipe to test whether a different sparse activation mechanism can reopen quality gains without introducing new code risk.","summary":"Run a `jumprelu` proxy comparison at K=128 under the stable signum/EF=16/aux-free regime, changing only architecture from gated to jumprelu.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This satisfies the severe-stagnation requirement by abandoning minor gated parameter tweaks and switching to a fundamentally different existing architecture family with prior full-signal evidence. It keeps the round isolated to one variable, avoids blocked code-fix paths, and uses proxy first.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation triggered an architecture pivot away from further gated-local tuning.","This round revisits the best existing non-gated family under the current strongest shared recipe to test whether the search failure is specific to gated rather than the whole regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` materially improves proxy FVU, promote it to full and treat it as the main alternative trunk for further stabilization.","If `jumprelu` remains clearly behind gated under the shared strong recipe, the next move should be a different architecture path or a narrow compatibility repair for an incubating family rather than more gated parameter sweeps."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0084_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The crash is a pure registration blocker: `residual_vq_topk` is missing from the architecture whitelist in `sparsify/config.py` and likely not wired into the factory path in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`. Patch only that registration path so the unchanged `K=32, EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` proxy can instantiate.","summary":"Apply a narrow registration repair for `residual_vq_topk` inside `sparsify/` and relaunch the exact same proxy target. Do not change the experiment recipe; only make the architecture name legal and constructible by the existing config/factory flow.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Convert the current unknown-architecture crash into a real startup/training signal for the original `residual_vq_topk` target.","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a tight repair scoped directly to the observed `Unknown architecture` error. It preserves the original experiment exactly and avoids mixing in any new search variable.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"residual_vq_topk","K":"32","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 84 repair attempt 1 targets only the concrete registration failure for `residual_vq_topk`; no recipe changes are allowed.","Observed blocker: `ValueError: Unknown architecture: 'residual_vq_topk'` raised in `sparsify/config.py::__post_init__` before training starts.","Keep follow-up repairs, if needed, constrained to making the existing architecture constructible under the unchanged launcher path."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registration repair works and the run completes, evaluate `residual_vq_topk` on quality before any further edits.","If a new concrete constructor or DDP compatibility error appears after registration is fixed, do one more pinpoint repair on the same target.","If the repaired prototype runs and is clearly weak, archive it on quality grounds rather than extending repair work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0137.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002low-rank trunk \u57fa\u5e93 U\u3001soft codebook \u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u90fd\u662f\u9759\u6001\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u7684\u56fa\u5b9a\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u65f6 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002\u6700\u8fd1 r132/r133/r136 \u5728\u6539 AUXK_ALPHA\u3001TRUNK_RANK\u3001NUM_CODES \u540e\u5f97\u5230\u51e0\u4e4e\u5b8c\u5168\u76f8\u540c\u7684 start/mid/end FVU\u3001tokens_per_sec \u4e0e final_total_tokens\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u5f53\u524d\u66f4\u9700\u8981\u5148\u8865\u4e00\u8f6e\u65e0\u9644\u52a0\u6210\u672c\u8f74\u6270\u52a8\u7684 clean baseline\uff0c\u786e\u8ba4\u4e3b\u7ebf reference recipe \u7684\u771f\u5b9e\u66f2\u7ebf\u4e0e\u8fd0\u884c\u4ee3\u4ef7\uff0c\u518d\u51b3\u5b9a\u4e0b\u4e00\u8f6e\u662f\u5411\u4e0a\u8fd8\u662f\u5411\u4e0b\u5fae\u8c03 LR\u3002",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0081.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`residual_vq_topk` still has not produced a real low-K signal because the prototype failed at the implementation layer before training, so the next move is one more narrow code-fix pass to make the existing `K=32`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` experiment runnable without changing its design.","summary":"Do a repair-focused pass on the existing `residual_vq_topk` prototype under `sparsify/` so the original proxy target can actually launch and survive sanity/startup. Keep the family, tier, and override set fixed; only patch the concrete implementation blocker.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This stays within the crash-repair-first rule and does not spend another round on parameter churn. The prototype has not earned a quality verdict yet because it has not run successfully, so one more narrow repair attempt is more informative than abandoning or redesigning it immediately.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["`residual_vq_topk` remains an implementation-blocked prototype rather than a judged architecture result until it completes a real run.","Keep repair scope narrow and confined to startup/sanity compatibility for the existing experiment target; do not redesign the family during repair.","If the next repair succeeds and the run completes, judge the family on quality; if it fails again with a new concrete blocker, continue only with another narrowly scoped repair."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq_topk` launches and completes, evaluate whether the discrete coarse-plus-residual framing is competitive enough to keep incubating at low K.","If a new concrete forward/backward or DDP compatibility error appears, do one more narrow repair pass with the same experiment target rather than changing architecture or overrides.","If the repaired prototype runs cleanly but is clearly weak, archive `residual_vq_topk` on quality grounds and pivot to a different fundamentally different family."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0058_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `K=40`, `EF=8` regime now appears broadly exhausted on quality and `codebook_topk` additionally exposed a concrete distributed-training compatibility failure, so the least-bad next move is a narrow code-fix round rather than another blind architecture swap. Repairing `codebook_topk` so all trainable paths participate in loss is the smallest informative step to determine whether the discrete-retrieval direction is actually bad or was obscured by a DDP-unused-parameter bug.","summary":"Patched `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` so `codebook_topk` uses a straight-through hard routing path for coarse code selection, preserving the original hard code choice in the forward pass while restoring gradients to `code_router.weight` and `code_router.bias`. Local `py_compile` passed and a direct backward check showed nonzero grads on the router parameters, so the original proxy recipe should now run without the prior DDP unused-parameter crash.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Eliminate the training crash and recover a valid proxy FVU for `codebook_topk` at the unchanged `K=40`, `EF=8` target.","family_name":"codebook_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"Kept the fix architecture-local and minimal inside `CodebookTopKSparseCoder._select_code`, without touching launcher, trainer, or experiment settings. Verified syntax and confirmed the previously unused router parameters now receive gradients in a local backward pass.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"codebook_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 repair attempt 1: fixed `codebook_topk` DDP unused-parameter failure in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` by replacing pure `argmax`/`index_select` routing with a straight-through hard assignment over `softmax(code_router(x))` so `code_router.weight` and `code_router.bias` stay in the gradient graph.","Local validation after the patch: `python -m py_compile sparsify/sparse_coder.py` passed, and a direct backward check on `CodebookTopKSparseCoder` produced nonzero grads for `code_router.weight` and `code_router.bias`, matching the suspected root cause from parameter indices 3 and 4 in the crash log."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `codebook_topk` proxy run completes and is competitive, promote it before any family-local tuning.","If the repaired run completes but is clearly weak, treat the current `K=40`, `EF=8` comparison band as broadly exhausted and pivot next to a more radical architecture or objective reformulation rather than another nearby variant.","If the repaired run still crashes, inspect for any remaining architecture-local parameters that are conditionally disconnected under the training loss before changing experiment design."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0080_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Patch the existing `residual_vq_topk` prototype registration so the original low-K proxy experiment can instantiate and run under the unchanged `K=32`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` target.","summary":"Repair the concrete launcher blocker by adding `residual_vq_topk` to architecture validation and SAE factory dispatch under `sparsify/`, without changing the experiment target or override set.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair stays narrowly scoped to the observed blocker: the new architecture name was not registered, so training failed before startup. The experiment design, family, and overrides remain unchanged.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 addresses a concrete registration blocker: `residual_vq_topk` was missing from config validation and SAE class dispatch.","Keep the experiment target fixed during repair; do not change family, tier, or env overrides until the prototype can launch.","If this registration repair succeeds but a new runtime error appears, handle that as the next narrow implementation blocker rather than redesigning the experiment."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registration repair works and the run completes, evaluate `residual_vq_topk` on its original low-K proxy merits before any follow-up.","If a new concrete implementation or DDP compatibility error appears after registration, do one additional narrow repair pass with the same experiment target.","If the repaired prototype runs and is clearly weak, archive the family on quality grounds rather than continuing repair-only work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0197.json:52:      "\u82e5 gated \u4ecd\u660e\u663e\u52a3\u4e8e lowrank_residual / lowrank_soft_codebook_residual\uff0c\u5219\u4e0b\u4e00\u8f6e\u56de\u5230\u4e3b\u7ebf\uff0c\u53ea\u8c03\u4e00\u4e2a\u6210\u672c\u8f74\u5982 TRUNK_RANK\u3001NUM_CODES \u6216 STAGE1_RATIO\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:19:    "hypothesis": "最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。当前 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 仍满足 ≤1.5×h×n 硬约束。r133 把 `TRUNK_RANK` 降到 32 时几乎零损失复现了主线 FVU，r182-r184 继续压缩 `NUM_CODES` 也未改变终点，说明当前主线可能仍有明显结构冗余。本轮只回答一个问题：将 `TRUNK_RANK` 进一步下调到 16，是否仍能保持接近当前主线的训练曲线与终点 FVU，同时继续降低 trunk 相关的 encoder 选择成本与部署查表成本，从而推动兼容 Pareto 前沿向更低总成本移动。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:20:    "summary": "继续围绕同一主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `TRUNK_RANK` 从已验证无损的 32 再降到 16，测试更激进的 trunk 压缩是否仍能维持当前 LUTurbo 可部署质量。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:25:    "self_review": "本轮严格遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 全部固定，只推进 `TRUNK_RANK` 这一直接作用于 encoder 选择成本和部署 trunk 成本的主变量。相比继续尝试在 policy 上有风险的 optimizer 分支，这一步更稳、更可归因，也更贴近 LUTurbo 的真实总成本目标。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:49:        "key": "TRUNK_RANK",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:55:      "family 与导出路径不变，`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 在 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 下仍是扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + two-stage residual 字典库的有限加权和。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:56:      "r133 表明 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 相对主线几乎无损，因此继续沿 trunk 容量轴下探比重复未增益的 `NUM_CODES` 压缩更有信息价值。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:60:      "若 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 仍接近当前主线 FVU 且吞吐不恶化，可将更低 rank 视为新的低成本主线，并考虑继续下探或做一次 clean baseline 复验。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:61:      "若 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 明显退化，则说明 trunk 容量下限更接近 32，下一轮回到 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 并转向 `NUM_CODES` 或其他单一成本轴。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:82:    "description": "继续围绕同一主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `TRUNK_RANK` 从已验证无损的 32 再降到 16，测试更激进的 trunk 压缩是否仍能维持当前 LUTurbo 可部署质量。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:83:    "self_review": "本轮严格遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 全部固定，只推进 `TRUNK_RANK` 这一直接作用于 encoder 选择成本和部署 trunk 成本的主变量。相比继续尝试在 policy 上有风险的 optimizer 分支，这一步更稳、更可归因，也更贴近 LUTurbo 的真实总成本目标。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0186.json:97:    "invalid_reason": "Audit confirmed that requested runtime parameters did not reach the actual training config: TRUNK_RANK=16 was requested, but checkpoint config saved None. This round should not be treated as a valid experimental record.",
