research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0065.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`preconditioned_topk` did not fail on quality but on architecture registration, so the next informative move is a narrow code-path repair that makes the new family selectable by the existing config/runtime path and then reruns the same `K=32`, `EF=8` probe unchanged.","summary":"Make a minimal `code_fix` for `preconditioned_topk` registration inside `sparsify/` so the runtime recognizes the architecture name, then rerun the same proxy recipe at `K=32`, `EF=8`. This preserves the preprocessing-oriented hypothesis and follows the repair-first rule for clear implementation blockers.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"preconditioned_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the right narrow follow-up because the last round produced no architecture signal at all. The risk is only that registration is not the sole issue, but this is still the smallest coherent repair before deciding whether to abandon the family.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"preconditioned_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 64 produced a pure implementation failure for `preconditioned_topk` (`Unknown architecture`), so this round is a repair-first follow-up rather than a quality verdict.","The repair target is architecture registration/dispatch for `preconditioned_topk` within `sparsify/`, after which the exact same `K=32`, `EF=8` proxy recipe should be rerun for a valid signal.","If the repaired `preconditioned_topk` still crashes, treat the family as blocked by implementation compatibility; if it runs and is weak, record preprocessing-oriented low-K fixes as another negative result in the small-EF band."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `preconditioned_topk` runs and is promising at `K=32`, `EF=8`, keep the family fixed and compare a nearby K such as `K=40` before touching EF.","If the repaired `preconditioned_topk` runs and is weak, pivot to another fundamentally different low-K family, likely a mixture-style or output-aware direction, rather than increasing expansion factor."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0080.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After repeated weak low-K results from routing, gated-branch, preprocessing, and thresholded-sparsity pivots, the next informative move is to switch from continuous sparse support selection to a discrete coarse-plus-residual representation. Add a new `residual_vq_topk` prototype under `sparsify/` and run it at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe to test whether a hard codebook backbone plus sparse residual correction yields a stronger low-K tradeoff than the current continuous families.","summary":"Implement a new prototype family `residual_vq_topk` in `sparsify/` and launch a proxy comparison at `K=32`, `EF=12` using minimal launcher-safe overrides. This is a fundamentally different architecture direction, keeps K as the priority, stays in the preferred EF band, and avoids more minor tuning on exhausted families.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a real search-direction pivot rather than another local sweep. The recent low-K failures suggest the current continuous sparse mechanisms may be fundamentally mismatched, so a discrete codebook-plus-residual prototype is the least-bad next experiment. Risk: first-pass codebook routing may be rough, but prototype proxy is the right tier for establishing whether this representation family is worth incubation.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Thirty no-improve rounds indicate the current low-K continuous-sparsity search direction may be fundamentally flawed.","A discrete coarse-codebook plus sparse-residual prototype is the next major architecture pivot after recent weak low-K routing/gating/preconditioning/JumpReLU results.","Keep the prototype launcher-safe and minimal: register the new architecture cleanly and avoid nonessential override keys."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq_topk` at `K=32, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `residual_vq_topk` crashes with a clear compatibility or DDP issue, do one narrow repair-focused follow-up rather than treating it as an architecture verdict.","If `residual_vq_topk` runs but is clearly weak, archive this discrete coarse-plus-residual direction and pivot again rather than returning to minor tweaks on archived low-K families."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0084.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`batch_topk` at `K=32, EF=12` was clearly weak, so the next informative move is to revive the still-untested discrete residual direction rather than keep sweeping known-poor low-K mechanisms. Do one narrow repair-focused pass on `residual_vq_topk` so the original `K=32, EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` proxy can actually instantiate and run.","summary":"Repair and relaunch the blocked `residual_vq_topk` proxy at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged low-K recipe. This preserves the fundamentally different architecture direction, keeps the comparison in the preferred EF band, and converts the current unknown-architecture blocker into a real quality signal.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Unblock a strategically different low-K family and obtain its first comparable proxy FVU; any clean run is more informative than another retune on families already shown weak.","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the highest-value unresolved architecture branch left: it is genuinely different and has not received a valid quality read yet, but the round only pays off if the fix is truly narrow and the launcher sees the registration.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"residual_vq_topk","K":"32","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 83: `batch_topk` at `K=32, EF=12` completed cleanly but was very weak (`FVU 0.42549`), so archive it as a competitive low-K candidate.","`residual_vq_topk` remains strategically valuable because it is a fundamentally different discrete/codebook-style residual direction, and its prior outcomes were implementation blockers rather than quality verdicts.","Keep the repair pass strictly narrow: preserve the original proxy target and avoid mixing in new hyperparameter changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq_topk` launches and is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before any EF move.","If it launches but is clearly weak, archive it on quality grounds and pivot to an input-space or output-aware architecture direction rather than another TopK mechanism tweak.","If it still fails with a new concrete compatibility error, do at most one more pinpoint repair on the same target; do not broaden the edit scope."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0004_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`jumprelu` under the strongest shared recipe remained far behind the gated frontier, so the next non-incremental move is to unblock a genuinely different architecture path rather than keep retuning known families. The `lowrank_residual` family has not produced any quality signal yet because it failed on architecture registration, so a narrow compatibility repair plus a proxy run is the most informative way to test whether removing a shared low-rank trunk before sparse coding can break the current stagnation.","summary":"Repair `lowrank_residual` architecture registration/compatibility under `sparsify/` and run a K=128 proxy comparison on the stable signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"Repair attempt 1 fixed the concrete blocker by registering `lowrank_residual` in config validation and the SAE factory, and by adding a minimal save/load-compatible prototype implementation with successful local config and forward/backward sanity checks. The experiment design, tier, family, and env overrides are unchanged.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 resolved the reported unknown-architecture blocker by adding `lowrank_residual` to config validation and `_get_sae_class`.","A minimal `LowRankResidualSparseCoder` prototype now exists and passed local instantiation plus forward/backward sanity, so the next run should reach training instead of failing at argument parsing."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `lowrank_residual` run now reaches training and yields competitive proxy FVU, keep the family alive for stabilization of the low-rank trunk/residual split.","If a new concrete runtime or sanity error appears, continue repair mode on that specific blocker without changing the experiment target."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0177.json:54:      "Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0177.json:64:    "termination_reason": "\u9009\u62e9\u6210\u672c\u8d85\u51fa\u9884\u7b97\uff1arouted_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual (K=128, EF=2) \u7684 encoder \u6210\u672c\u4e3a 2.25x \u539f\u59cb\u77e9\u9635\uff0c\u9884\u7b97\u6bd4\u7387 1.5x\uff08\u9700 \u22641.0x\uff0c\u5373 \u22641.5\u00d7h\u00d7n\uff09\u3002\u8bf7\u901a\u8fc7\u51cf\u5c0f K / EXPANSION_FACTOR / TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES \u7b49\u53c2\u6570\u964d\u4f4e\u9009\u62e9\u6210\u672c\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0177.json:65:    "description": "\u9009\u62e9\u6210\u672c\u8d85\u51fa\u9884\u7b97\uff1arouted_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual (K=128, EF=2) \u7684 encoder \u6210\u672c\u4e3a 2.25x \u539f\u59cb\u77e9\u9635\uff0c\u9884\u7b97\u6bd4\u7387 1.5x\uff08\u9700 \u22641.0x\uff0c\u5373 \u22641.5\u00d7h\u00d7n\uff09\u3002\u8bf7\u901a\u8fc7\u51cf\u5c0f K / EXPANSION_FACTOR / TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES \u7b49\u53c2\u6570\u964d\u4f4e\u9009\u62e9\u6210\u672c\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0126.json:19:    "hypothesis": "最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j，其中 U(Vx) 对应可静态导出的 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，最终仍可落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，因此兼容性为扩展兼容。当前主线已确认 EF=2 在预算内，而 signum/LR/K 轴最近几轮没有带来改进，本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变的前提下，下调 TRUNK_RANK 到 32，能否进一步压低 encoder 选择成本并维持可接受的 FVU，从而得到更优的 Pareto 权衡。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0126.json:20:    "summary": "保持 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 主线与 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，仅下调 TRUNK_RANK 到 32，测试是否能以有限 FVU 损失换取更低 encoder 成本和更好的 LUTurbo 总体权衡。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0126.json:25:    "self_review": "本轮严格只改一个主变量，并把探索重心从已基本洗净的 signum/LR/K 轴转向更贴近 Pareto 目标的 selection-cost 轴。风险在于 TRUNK_RANK=32 可能过于激进，但它能最快回答该 family 是否还有内部压缩空间。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0126.json:49:        "key": "TRUNK_RANK",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0126.json:60:      "若 TRUNK_RANK=32 仅小幅伤害 FVU 但明显降低 selection_cost，则继续沿 trunk_rank 轴补一个中间点以细化 Pareto。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0126.json:61:      "若 TRUNK_RANK=32 明显恶化 FVU 且时间收益有限，则恢复默认 trunk 配方，转向 loss/preprocess 轴。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0126.json:62:      "若 TRUNK_RANK=32 同时改善时间与 selection_cost，但 FVU 退化可接受，则把它作为低成本分支保留，不再继续降 K。"
