research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0032.json:1:{"command":"edit_sae_code","hypothesis":"`routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` likely has a training-time compatibility bug under the fixed launcher despite earlier smoke success; repairing that runtime failure and rerunning the same `K=16, EF=12` recipe is the highest-value next step because the architecture comparison is currently blocked by implementation stability rather than scientific signal.","summary":"Fix the `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` training crash inside `sparsify/`, then rerun the exact same architecture-only comparison at `K=16, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` so the round resolves the blocker instead of opening another branch.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"stability","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"incubating","self_review":"This follows the runtime-priority policy: the most recent architecture trial crashed early, so the next round should repair compatibility rather than launch another minor sweep or a different architecture. Keeping the same recipe after the fix preserves a single scientific question, with code repair serving only to unblock the architecture comparison.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/config.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 31 crashed on `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=16` before producing a usable comparison; round 32 should focus on fixing the architecture's training-time compatibility in `sparsify/` and then rerun the exact same recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` runs cleanly and beats the current `K=16` point, continue the same architecture-only comparison at `K=24`.","If it runs cleanly but loses at `K=16`, keep the result as a valid negative and switch to a different substantial architecture branch next round.","If the rerun still crashes after a targeted fix, treat the family as blocked on engineering reliability and move to another fundamentally different architecture."],"primary_variable":"code_edit"}
